					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7337949#post-4014722</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7337949/scp-4656#post-4014722</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Fri, 05 Oct 2018 13:13:45 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ModernMajorGeneral</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>274283</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I like this a lot. It's difficult to understand what's going on here, and I suspect I haven't got it exactly right (if there is even a 'right' way to understand this) but this is one of the rare SCPs where using a lot of dense jargon doesn't stop it from being unsettling and vaguely upsetting.</p> <p>I especially like the visual/stylistic device of 'there is no connection' being the phrase that forms the connection holding the piece together, which is simple and neat and contrasts nicely with the rest. +1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
